    Class and Attributes list

    HLAobjectRoot

    Sharing: N

    Attributes

    Name Data type Semantics Sharing Order Transportation
    HLAprivilegeToDeleteObject NA N TimeStamp HLAreliable

    ActiveSonarBeam

    Inherits from HLAobjectRoot

    A sector of concentrated energy from a device that radiates an active sonar signal.

    Sharing: N

    Attributes

    Name Data type Semantics Sharing Order Transportation
    ActiveEmissionParameterIndex HLAinteger16BEN_slsh_Aperfectalways1 An index into the database of active (intentional) underwater acoustics emissions. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    AzimuthBeamwidth HLAfloat32BEradiansperfectalways The horizontal beam width of the main beam (as opposed to any side lobes) measured at the 3 dB down point of peak radiated power level. Omni directional beams shall have a beam width of 0 radians. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    AzimuthCenter HLAfloat32BEradiansperfectalways The center azimuthal bearing of the main beam (as opposed to side lobes) in relation to the emitter coordinate system. Omnidirection beams shall have an azimuthal center of 0 radians. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    BeamIdentifier HLAoctetN_slsh_Aperfectalways1 The identification of the active sonar beam, which must be unique on the active sonar system. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    ElevationBeamwidth HLAfloat32BEradiansperfectalways TBD N Receive HLAbestEffort
    ElevationCenter HLAfloat32BEradiansperfectalways TBD N Receive HLAbestEffort
    EventIdentifier EventIdentifierStruct TBD N Receive HLAbestEffort
    ScanPattern ActiveSonarScanPatternEnum16 The pattern that describes the movement of the sonar beam of the emitter. N Receive HLAbestEffort

    Inherited attributes

    Name Data type Semantics Sharing Order Transportation
    HLAprivilegeToDeleteObject NA N TimeStamp HLAreliable

    BaseEntity

    Inherits from HLAobjectRoot

    Sharing: N

    Attributes

    Name Data type Semantics Sharing Order Transportation
    EntityType EntityTypeStruct The category of the entity. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    EntityIdentifier EntityIdentifierStruct The unique identifier for the entity instance. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    IsPartOf IsPartOfStruct Defines if the entity if a constituent part of another entity (denoted the host entity). If the entity is a constituent part of another entity then the ParentEntityID shall be set to the EntityID of the host entity and the ParentRTIObjectID shall be set to the RTO object ID of the host entity. If the entity is not a constituent part of another entity then the ParentEntityID shall being set to 0.0.0 and the ParentRTIObjectID shall be set to the empty string. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    Spatial SpatialStruct Spatial state stored in one variant record attribute N Receive HLAbestEffort
    RelativeSpatial SpatialStruct Relative spatial state stored in one variant record attribute N Receive HLAbestEffort

    Inherited attributes

    Name Data type Semantics Sharing Order Transportation
    HLAprivilegeToDeleteObject NA N TimeStamp HLAreliable

    AggregateEntity

    Inherits from HLAobjectRoot.BaseEntity

    Sharing: N

    Attributes

    Name Data type Semantics Sharing Order Transportation
    AggregateMarking AggregateMarkingStruct A unique marking or combination of characters used to distinguish the aggregate from other aggregates. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    AggregateState AggregateStateEnum8 An indicator of the extent of association of objects form an operating group. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    Dimensions DimensionStruct The size of the area covered by the units in the aggregate. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    EntityIdentifiers RTIObjectIdArrayStruct The identification of entities that are contained within the aggregate. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    ForceIdentifier ForceIdentifierEnum8 The identification of the force that the aggregate belongs to. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    Formation FormationEnum32 The category of positional arrangement of the entities within the aggregate. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    NumberOfSilentEntities HLAinteger16BEN_slsh_Aperfectalways1 The number of elements in the SilentEntities list N Receive HLAbestEffort
    NumberOfVariableDatums Unsignedinteger32BEN_slsh_Aperfectalways1 The number of records in the Variable Datum structure N Receive HLAbestEffort
    SilentAggregates ArrayOfSilentAggregateStructDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray The numbers and types, of slient aggregates contained in the aggregate. Silent aggregates are sub-aggregates that are in the aggregate, but that are not separately represented in the virtual world. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    SilentEntities ArrayOfSilentEntityStructDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray The numbers and types, of silent entities in the aggregate. Silent entites are entities that are in the aggregate, but that are not separately represented in the virtual world. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    SubAggregateIdentifiers RTIObjectIdArrayStruct The identifications of aggregates represented in the virtual world that are contained in the aggregate. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    VariableDatums ArrayOfVariableDatumStructDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Extra data that describes the aggregate. N Receive HLAbestEffort

    NETN_Aggregate

    Inherits from HLAobjectRoot.BaseEntity.AggregateEntity

    Aggregate extensions for NETN

    Sharing: PS

    Attributes

    Name Data type Semantics Sharing Order Transportation
    UnitPersonnel ResourceStatusArray This summarizes the health status of personnel comprising the aggregate. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    Callsign HLAunicodeString The name of the object. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    VisualSignature VisualSignatureStruct Describes the unit's susceptibility to electro-optical detection. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    SourceUnit HLAunicodeString Aggregate from which this aggregate was spawned. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    Mission MissionStruct The operational task the aggregate has been ordered to perform. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    Mounted NETN_Float64BE The percentage of aggregate personnel traveling on or in their organic transport. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    UnitSupplies SupplyArray The type and quantities of supplies available (on hand) to the unit. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    HigherHeadquarters NETN_UniqueID A pointer to the aggregate's superior unit or headquarters. The highest level unit or headquarters on each side will publish its own UniqueID as its HigherHeadquarters value. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    CombatValue NETN_Float64BE A summary value (in percent) of unit effectiveness based on level of training, leadership, moral, personnel and equipment operational status, etc. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    WeaponsControlOrder WeaponControlOrderEnum8 Describes current Weapon Control Order Free, Tight, or Hold. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    SupportUnit SupportRelationshipStruct Identifies unit(s) which support the aggregate logistically, or with a specified combat or combat support relationship, e.g. a Direct Support or General Support Artillery unit. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    Activity AggregateMissionEnum16 The current activity of the aggregate. This may differ from the mission due to casualties, readiness, etc. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    Symbol HLAunicodeString The APP6A code for the aggregate. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    CaptureStatus CaptureStatusEnum8 The status of an aggregate with respect to its control or influence over its own activites. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    UnitEquipment ResourceStatusArray This summarizes the health status of the equipment comprising the aggregate. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    Echelon EchelonEnum8 The level of command of the aggregate. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    HUMINTSignature HUMINTSignatureStruct Describes the unit's susceptibility to human intelligence (HUMINT), i.e. information collected and provided by human sources. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    ElectronicSignature ElectronicSignatureStruct Describes the aggregate's susceptibility to electronic detection both as a summary value and by identifying aggregate sensors together with their operational status. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    Footprint WorldLocationStructArray3 The region occupied by the aggregate. the region is defined as that bounded by line segments connecting the listed world locations. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    CoverStatus CoverStatusStruct Describes the unit's protection from the effects of weapons fire. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    EntityList EntityListVariableLengthStruct Provides data on entities comprising the aggregate. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    Status ActiveStatusEnum8 If an instance shall be taken into account by federates N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    UniqueID NETN_UniqueID The unique identifier of the object. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort
    EmbeddedUnitList ArrayOfEmbeddedUnit The list of objects carried by this aggregate. N TimeStamp HLAbestEffort

If the entity is not a constituent part of another entity then the ParentEntityID shall being set to 0.0.0 and the ParentRTIObjectID shall be set to the empty string. N Receive HLAbestEffort
    Spatial SpatialStruct Spatial state stored in one variant record attribute N Receive HLAbestEffort

If the entity is not a constituent part of another entity then the ParentEntityID shall being set to 0.0.0 and the ParentRTIObjectID shall be set to the empty string. N Receive HLAbestEffort

    HLAfederate

    Inherits from HLAobjectRoot.HLAmanager

    This object class shall contain RTI state variables relating to a joined federate. The RTI shall publish it and shall register one object instance for each joined federate in a federation. Dynamic attributes that shall be contained in an object instance shall be updated periodically, where the period should be determined by an interaction of the class HLAmanager. HLAfederate.HLAadjust.HLAsetTiming. If this value is never set or is set to zero, no periodic up-date shall be performed by the RTI.

    Sharing: P

    Attributes

    Name Data type Semantics Sharing Order Transportation
    HLAfederateHandle HLAhandle Handle of the joined federate returned by a Join Federation Execution service invocation P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAfederateType HLAunicodeString Type of the joined federate specified by the joined federate when it joined the federation P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAfederateHost HLAunicodeString Host name of the computer on which the joined federate is executing P Receive HLAreliable
    HLARTIversion HLAunicodeString Version of the RTI software being used P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAFDDID HLAunicodeString Identifier associated with the FDD data used by the joined federate P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAtimeConstrained HLAboolean Whether the time advance of the joined federate is constrained by other joined federates P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAtimeRegulating HLAboolean Whether the joined federate influences the time advancement of other joined federates P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAasynchronousDelivery HLAboolean Whether the RTI shall deliver receive-order messages to the joined federate while the joined federate's time manager state is not Time Advancing (only matters if the joined federate is time-constrained) P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAfederateState HLAfederateState State of the joined federate P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAtimeManagerState HLAtimeState State of the joined federate's time manager P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAlogicalTime HLAlogicalTime Joined federate's logical time. Initial value of this information is initial value of time of the Time Representation Abstract datatype (TRADT). P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAlookahead HLAtimeInterval Minimum duration into the future that a TSO message will be scheduled. The value shall not be defined if the joined federate is not time-regulating) P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAGALT HLAlogicalTime Joined federate's Greatest Available Logical Time (GALT). The value shall not be defined if GALT is not defined for the joined federate. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLALITS HLAlogicalTime Joined federate's Least Incoming Time Stamp (LITS). The value shall not be defined if LITS is not defined for the joined federate. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAROlength HLAcount Number of RO messages queued for delivery to the joined federate. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLATSOlength HLAcount Number of TSO messages queued for delivery to the joined federate P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAreflectionsReceived HLAcount Total number of reflections received by the joined federate. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAupdatesSent HLAcount Total number of updates sent by the joined federate P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAinteractionsReceived HLAcount Total number of interactions received by the joined federate. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAinteractionsSent HLAcount Total number of interactions sent by the joined federate. This information shall reflect related DDM usage. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAobjectInstancesThatCanBeDeleted HLAcount Total number of object instances whose HLAprivilegeToDeleteObject attribute is owned by the joined federate P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAobjectInstancesUpdated HLAcount Total number of object instances for which the joined federate has invoked the Update Attribute Values service. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAobjectInstancesReflected HLAcount Total number of object instances for which the joined federate has had a Reflect Attribute Values service invocation. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAobjectInstancesDeleted HLAcount Total number of times the Delete Object Instance service was invoked by the joined federate since the federate joined the federation P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAobjectInstancesRemoved HLAcount Total number of times the Remove Object Instance service was invoked for the joined federate since the federate joined the federation. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAobjectInstancesRegistered HLAcount Total number of times the Register Object Instance or Register Object Instance with Region service was invoked by the joined federate since the federate joined the federation. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAobjectInstancesDiscovered HLAcount Total number of times the Discover Object Instance service was invoked for the joined federate since the federate joined the federation P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAtimeGrantedTime HLAmsec Wall clock time duration that the federate has spent in the Time Granted state since the last update of this attribute. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAtimeAdvancingTime HLAmsec Wall clock time duration that the federate has spent in the Time Advancing state since the last update of this attribute. P Receive HLAreliable
    HLAconveyRegionDesignatorSets HLAswitch Value of federation-wide Convey Region Designator Sets Switch. Updated when value of switch changes P Receive HLAreliable

    Parameters

    Name Data type Semantics
    Type HLAunicodeString A string which identify the type of named signal. The possible values must be defined in a dictionary according to the needs (to be described in the GRIM). This field is not specified through Enum value to keep flexibility. Example of value: MagicAction, WhiteCellAction, etc.
    Identifier HLAunicodeString ID of the named signal.According to the Type of signal chosen, this field allows to refer the activate element (Platform ID, Melmil element ID, etc)
    Activated HLAboolean State of the named signal. Allows to manage the action carried by the named signal
    ComplementDataBoolean HLAboolean Complementary Data of Boolean typeDefault value is 0.
    ComplementDataFloat HLAfloat32BE Complementary Data of Float typeDefault value is 0.
    ComplementDataString HLAunicodeString Complementary Data of String type. This field will be able to contain XML formatted informations according to the needs.Default value must be contains the minimal TAG (see GRIM)

    Inherits HLAinteractionRoot.Collision
    Semantics The act or instance of coming together with solid impact in an elastic manner. An elastic collision allows a higher fidelity collision to be modeled, taking into account linear and rotational momentum transfer, variable elasticity, and momentum transfer that is dependent on surface orientation.

    Transportation HLAbestEffort

    IntermediateResultXY HLAfloat32BEN_slsh_Aperfectalways X-Y Component of the positive semi-definite Collision Intermediate Result matrix
    IntermediateResultXZ HLAfloat32BEN_slsh_Aperfectalways X-Z Component of the positive semi-definite Collision Intermediate Result matrix
    IntermediateResultYY HLAfloat32BEN_slsh_Aperfectalways Y-Y Component of the positive semi-definite Collision Intermediate Result matrix
    IntermediateResultYZ HLAfloat32BEN_slsh_Aperfectalways Y-Z Component of the positive semi-definite Collision Intermediate Result matrix
    IntermediateResultZZ HLAfloat32BEN_slsh_Aperfectalways Z-Z Component of the positive semi-definite Collision Intermediate Result matrix
    UnitSurfaceNormal EntityCoordinateVectorStruct The normal vector to the surface at the point of collision detection

    HLAmodifyAttributeState

    Properties

    Identifier HLAinteractionRoot.HLAmanager.HLAfederate.HLAadjust.HLAmodifyAttributeState
    Inherits HLAinteractionRoot.HLAmanager.HLAfederate.HLAadjust
    Semantics Modify the ownership state of an attribute of an object instance for the specified joined federate. If the interaction is used to give ownership of the instance attribute to the specified joined federate and another joined federate currently owns the instance attribute, the owning joined federate shall be divested of ownership of the instance attribute before ownership is granted to the specified joined federate. No notification of change of ownership of the instance attribute shall be provided to either joined federate. In order for ownership of the instance attribute to be granted to the specified joined federate, the following conditions shall be true: - the specified joined federate knows about the object instance - the specified joined federate is publishing the corresponding class attribute at the known class of the specified object instance at that joined federate - the specified instance attribute is not owned by the RTI (i.e., it's not a predefined attribute of a MOM object class) If one or more of the above conditions are not met, then the interaction shall have no effect and an error shall be reported via an interaction of class HLAmanager. HLAfederate.HLAreport. HLAreportMOMexception.
    Sharing S
    Order Receive
    Transportation HLAreliable

    Parameters

    Name Data type Semantics
    HLAobjectInstance HLAhandle Handle of the object instance whose attribute state is being changed
    HLAattribute HLAhandle Handle of the instance attribute whose stateis being changed
    HLAattributeState HLAownership New state for the attribute of the object instance

    Inherited parameters

    Name Data type Semantics
    HLAfederate HLAhandle Handle of the joined federate that was provided when joining.

    HLAreportServiceInvocation

    Properties

    Identifier HLAinteractionRoot.HLAmanager.HLAfederate.HLAreport.HLAreportServiceInvocation
    Inherits HLAinteractionRoot.HLAmanager.HLAfederate.HLAreport
    Semantics This interaction shall be sent by the RTI whenever an HLA service is invoked, either by the indicated joined federate or by the RTI at the indicated joined federate, and Service Reporting is Enabled for the indicated joined federate. This interaction shall always contain the arguments supplied by the service invoker. If the service invocation was successful, the interaction also shall contain the value returned to the invoker (if the service returns a value); otherwise, the interaction also shall contain an indication of the exception that shall be raised to the invoker.
    Sharing P
    Order Receive
    Transportation HLAreliable

    Parameters

    Name Data type Semantics
    HLAservice HLAunicodeString Textual name of the service
    HLAsuccessIndicator HLAboolean Whether the service invocation was successful. Exception values are returned along with HLAfalse value
    HLAsuppliedArguments HLAargumentList Textual depiction of the arguments supplied in the service invocation
    HLAreturnedArguments HLAargumentList Textual depiction of the argument returned by the service invocation (null if the service does not normally return a value or if HLAsuccessIndicator is HLAfalse)
    HLAexception HLAunicodeString Textual depiction of the exception raised by this service invocation (null if HLAsuccessIndicator is HLAtrue)
    HLAserialNumber HLAcount This is a per-joined federate serial number that shall start at zero and shall increment by 1 for each HLAmanager.HLAfederate.HLAreport HLAreportServiceInvocation interaction that represents service invocations to or from the respective joined federate.

    HLAservice

    Properties

    Identifier HLAinteractionRoot.HLAmanager.HLAfederate.HLAservice
    Inherits HLAinteractionRoot.HLAmanager.HLAfederate
    Semantics The interaction class shall be acted upon by the RTI. These interactions shall invoke HLA services on behalf of another joined federate. They shall cause the RTI to react as if the service has invoked by that other joined federate. If exceptions arise as a result of the use of these interactions, they shall be reported via the HLAmanager. HLAfederate.HLAreport.HLAreportMOMexception interaction to all joined federates that subscribe to this interaction. There are two ways an error can occur: the sending federate does not provide all the required arguments as parameters or the preconditions of the spoofed service are not met. Each type of error is reported via the HLAMOMreportMOMexception. NOTE?These interactions shall have the potential to disrupt normal federation execution and should be used with great care.
    Sharing N
    Order Receive
    Transportation HLAreliable

    Inherited parameters

    Name Data type Semantics
    HLAfederate HLAhandle Handle of the joined federate that was provided when joining.

    MinefieldData

    Properties

    Identifier HLAinteractionRoot.MinefieldData
    Inherits HLAinteractionRoot
    Semantics Provides information on individual mines contained within a minefield
    Sharing N
    Order TimeStamp
    Transportation HLAreliable

    Parameters

    Name Data type Semantics
    GroundBurialDepthOffset ArrayOfHLAfloat32BEmetresperfectalwaysDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the offset of the origin of the mine coordinate system with respect to the ground surface. This offset can be used in conjunction with the mine orienteation to determine the actual ground burial depth of the surfaces of a mine. Ground burial depth offset is specified as a positive measurement in meteres below the wate surface along the up vector.
    Fusing ArrayOfMineFusingStructDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the primary and secondary fuse and anti-handling device for each mine.
    MineEmplacementTime ArrayOfClockTimeStructDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the real-world, coordinated universal time (UTC) emplacement time of a mine.
    MineEntityIdentifier ArrayOfUnsignedinteger16BEperfectalwaysDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the mine entity identifier number. The mine identification in conjunction with the MinefieldID form the unique identifier for each mine.
    MinefieldIdentifier Unsignedinteger32BEN_slsh_AperfectalwaysN_slsh_A Identifies the minefield to which the mines belong
    MineLocation ArrayOfWorldLocationStructDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the location of the relative to the minfield location.
    MineOrientation ArrayOfOrientationStructDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the orientation of the center axis direction of fire of the mine, relative to the minefield Coordinate System. If any of the three burial depth offsets is sent in the Record , this field shall also be sent.
    MineType EntityTypeStruct Specifies the type of each mine contained within the minefield interaction
    NumberOfRecords HLAoctetN_slsh_AperfectalwaysN_slsh_A Specifies the total number of minefiled records being sent in response to a minefield Query interaction.
    NumberTripDetonationWires ArrayOfHLAoctetperfectalwaysDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the number of trip detonation wires that exist for each mine. I sub n designates the trip wire count for mine n of N.
    NumberWireVertices ArrayOfHLAoctetperfectalwaysDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the number of vertices are in each trip wire. A set of I sub n vertex counts is given for each mine n of N, iff I sub n > 0. If I sub n is 0, the vertex count set is empty. Each non empty set of vertex counts (I sub n > 0) follows the previous non empty set. J sub i designates the vertex count of tripwire i of I sub n.
    PaintScheme ArrayOfMinefieldPaintSchemeEnum32DynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the camouflage scheme and color of the mine.
    RecordSequenceNumber HLAoctetN_slsh_Aperfectalways1 Specifies the number of the current record in a sequence of minefiled records sent in response to a query interaction.
    Reflectance ArrayOfHLAfloat32BEperfectalwaysDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the local dielectric difference between the mine and the surrounding soil.
    RequestIdentifier HLAoctetN_slsh_Aperfectalways1 Identifies the matching response to a request for mine information from the minefield simulation made by means of a Query interaction
    RequestingEntityIdentifier Unsignedinteger32BEN_slsh_AperfectalwaysN_slsh_A Identifies the matching response to a request for mine information from the associated minefield object state.
    ScalarDetectionCoefficient ArrayOfHLAoctetperfectalwaysDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the coefficient to be utilized to insure proper correlation between detctors located on different simulation platforms. In statistically based detection system applications, the detection system simulation will generally compare a random number against an internally calculated probability of detection. There are M (number of sensors) coefficients for each of the N mines. Question: all of type 1 first then all of type 2 OR all of mine 1 first then mine 2.
    SensorTypes ArrayOfMinefieldSensorTypeEnum32DynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray In QRP mode, specifies the requesting sensor types which were specified in the minefield query. In heartbeat mode, specifies the sensor types that are bein served by the minefield.
    SnowBurialDepthOffset ArrayOfHLAfloat32BEmetresperfectalwaysDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the offset of the origin of the mine coordinate system with respect to the snow surface. This offset can be used in conjuncition with the mine orientation to determine the actual snow baurial depth of the survaces of a mine. Snow burial depth offset is specified as a positive measurement in meters below the snow surface along the up vector.
    ThermalContrast ArrayOfHLAfloat32BEDegrees_spc_CperfectalwaysDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the temperature difference between the mine and the surround soil in degrees Centigrade. In the case of a buried mine, the delta temperature shall be measured between the ground surface above the mine and the surrounding ground surface temperature.
    WaterBurialDepthOffset ArrayOfHLAfloat32BEmetresperfectalwaysDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the offset of the origin of the mine coordinate system with respect to the water surface. This offset can be used in conjunction with the mine orienteation to determine the actual water burial depth of the surfaces of a mine. Water burial depth offset is specified as a positive measurement in meteres below the wate surface along the up vector.
    WireVertices ArrayOfWorldLocationStructDynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Specifies the vertices in a trip wire. A set of J sub i vertices is given for each trip wire i of I sub n, iff I sub n is > 0 and J sub i > 0. If I sub n is 0 or J sub i is 0, the vertex set is empty. Each non empty set of verticies (J sub i > 0) follows the previous non empty set.

    Link16RadioSignal

    Properties

    Identifier HLAinteractionRoot.RadioSignal.RawBinaryRadioSignal.TDLBinaryRadioSignal.Link16RadioSignal
    Inherits HLAinteractionRoot.RadioSignal.RawBinaryRadioSignal.TDLBinaryRadioSignal
    Semantics Link-16 radio signal
    Sharing N
    Order Receive
    Transportation HLAreliable

    Parameters

    Name Data type Semantics
    NPGNumber UnsignedShort1 Network/Needline Participation Group (NPG) number. Used to segregate information within a JTIDS/MIDS network. Creates virtual networks of participants.
    NetNumber HLAoctet Network Number. Used to create virtual sub-circuits within NPG for stacked nets or between NPGs for multi-net.
    PerceivedTransmitTime LongLong1 The time at which the radio signal is transmitted
    TimeSlotID UnsignedLong1 Timeslot identification. Bit encoded field. Bits 0-16 denote the Timeslot number. Timeslot 0 represents timeslot A-1, timeslot 98303 represents C-32767. When the epoch is 112, the last valid timeslot is 45151 (end of the day). Bits 17-23 are padding and shall be set to 0. Bits 24-31 denote the Epoch Number. An epoch is 12.8 minutes long, 112.5 Epochs in a 24 hour day. Part of timeslot identification.
    TSEC_CVLL HLAoctet Transmission Security, an integer identification of the crypto variable used for JTIDS transmission encryption. This variable allows for simulated crypto netting. A value of 255 shall indicate a no statement/wildcard.
    MSEC_CVLL HLAoctet Message Security, an integer identification of the crypto variable used to encode the JTIDS message. This variable allows for simulated crypto netting. A value of 255 shall indicate a no statement/wildcard.

    Inherited parameters

    Name Data type Semantics
    HostRadioIndex RTIObjectIdStruct The ID of the radio transmitting this signal.
    DataRate Unsignedinteger32BEbits_slsh_secondperfectalways1 The rate at which the data is being transmitted.
    SignalDataLength Unsignedinteger16BEbitsperfectalways1 The length of the signal data.
    SignalData ArrayOfHLAoctetN_slsh_AperfectalwaysN_slsh_ADynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray The signal data.
    TacticalDataLinkType TacticalDataLinkTypeEnum16 The type of tactical data link used to transmitted this signal (if any).
    TDLMessageCount Unsignedinteger16BEN_slsh_Aperfectalways1 The number of tactical data link messages contained in this signal.

    Sharing N

    JTIDSHeader JTIDSHeaderStruct JTIDS Header
    Data octetArray3 Data

    Inherited parameters

    Name Data type Semantics
    NPGNumber UnsignedShort1 Network/Needline Participation Group (NPG) number. Used to segregate information within a JTIDS/MIDS network. Creates virtual networks of participants.
    NetNumber HLAoctet Network Number. Used to create virtual sub-circuits within NPG for stacked nets or between NPGs for multi-net.
    PerceivedTransmitTime LongLong1 The time at which the radio signal is transmitted
    TimeSlotID UnsignedLong1 Timeslot identification. Bit encoded field. Bits 0-16 denote the Timeslot number. Timeslot 0 represents timeslot A-1, timeslot 98303 represents C-32767. When the epoch is 112, the last valid timeslot is 45151 (end of the day). Bits 17-23 are padding and shall be set to 0. Bits 24-31 denote the Epoch Number. An epoch is 12.8 minutes long, 112.5 Epochs in a 24 hour day. Part of timeslot identification.
    TSEC_CVLL HLAoctet Transmission Security, an integer identification of the crypto variable used for JTIDS transmission encryption. This variable allows for simulated crypto netting. A value of 255 shall indicate a no statement/wildcard.
    MSEC_CVLL HLAoctet Message Security, an integer identification of the crypto variable used to encode the JTIDS message. This variable allows for simulated crypto netting. A value of 255 shall indicate a no statement/wildcard.
    HostRadioIndex RTIObjectIdStruct The ID of the radio transmitting this signal.
    DataRate Unsignedinteger32BEbits_slsh_secondperfectalways1 The rate at which the data is being transmitted.
    SignalDataLength Unsignedinteger16BEbitsperfectalways1 The length of the signal data.
    SignalData ArrayOfHLAoctetN_slsh_AperfectalwaysN_slsh_ADynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray The signal data.
    TacticalDataLinkType TacticalDataLinkTypeEnum16 The type of tactical data link used to transmitted this signal (if any).
    TDLMessageCount Unsignedinteger16BEN_slsh_Aperfectalways1 The number of tactical data link messages contained in this signal.

    Identifier HLAinteractionRoot.RecordQueryR
    Inherits HLAinteractionRoot
    Semantics A Simulation Managent (SIMAN) interaction designed to allow a Simulation Manager federate to request data, in record format, from another federate.
    Sharing N
    Order Receive
    Transportation HLAbestEffort

    Parameters

    Name Data type Semantics
    OriginatingEntity EntityIdentifierStruct The DIS entity ID of the entity or application sending the interaction.
    ReceivingEntity EntityIdentifierStruct The DIS entity ID of the entity or application which is the intended recipient of the interaction.
    RequestIdentifier Unsignedinteger32BEN_slsh_AperfectalwaysN_slsh_A The Request ID is a monotonically increasing integer identifier inserted by the Simulation Manager into all Simulation management interactions. It is used as a unique identifier to identify the latest in a series of competing requests and identifying acknowledgements.
    TimeInterval Unsignedinteger32BEperfectalways The interval between regular updates of the requested data. If this field is zero then the recipient should only issue a single RecordR interaction in response to this interaction.
    EventType EventTypeEnum32 Specifies the type of event that the receiving entity or application should use to trigger the issue of a RecordR interaction in response to this query. If this is zero, then reporting shall be periodic based upon the value of the TimeInterval parameter.
    AcknowledgementProtocol AcknowledgementProtocolEnum8 The acknowledgement protocol to be used for the transaction
    RecordIdentifiers ArrayOfDatumIdentifierEnum32DynamicHLAlengthlessVarArray Identifies the records for which information is requested

    Semantics Communicates information associated with the firing or launch of a munition.
    Sharing N
    Order Receive
    Transportation HLAbestEffort

    Parameters

    Name Data type Semantics
    EventIdentifier EventIdentifierStruct An ID, generated by the issuing federate, used to associated related fire and detonation events.
    FireControlSolutionRange HLAfloat32BEmetersperfectalways The range used in the fire control solution. Zero if the range is unknown or inapplicable.
    FireMissionIndex Unsignedinteger32BEN_slsh_AperfectalwaysN_slsh_A A unique index to identify the fire mission (used to associated weapon fire interactions in a single fire mission).
    FiringLocation WorldLocationStruct The location, the world coordinate system, of the weapon fire.
    FiringObjectIdentifier RTIObjectIdStruct The ID of the object ffiring the munition.
    FuseType FuseTypeEnum16 The type of fuse on the munition.
    InitialVelocityVector VelocityVectorStruct The velocity vector of the munition when fired.
    MunitionObjectIdentifier RTIObjectIdStruct The ID of the associated munition object (if any).
    MunitionType EntityTypeStruct The type of munition being fired.
    QuantityFired Unsignedinteger16BEN_slsh_AperfectalwaysN_slsh_A The number of rounds fired in the fire event.
    RateOfFire Unsignedinteger16BEN_slsh_AperfectalwaysN_slsh_A The rate of fire at which the munitions in the burst described in the fire event.
    TargetObjectIdentifier RTIObjectIdStruct The ID of the object being fired at (if any).
    WarheadType WarheadTypeEnum16 The type of warhead fitted to the munition being fired.

    ShaftDataStruct

    Semantics -NULL-
    Encoding -NULL-


    Fields
    Name Data type Semantics
    CurrentShaftRate HLAinteger16BERPMperfectalways1 The current shaft speed. A positive shaft speed indicates that the shaft is rotating in a clockwise direction (when viewed from the stern to bow), and a negative shaft speed indicates an anti-clockwise direction.
    OrderedShaftRate HLAinteger16BERPMperfectalways1 The ordered shaft speed. If the ordered shaft speed is different from the current shaft speed then the shaft will accelerate or decelerate at the shaft rate of change. A positive shaft speed indicates that the shaft is rotating in a clockwise direction (when viewed from the stern to bow), and a negative shaft speed indicates an anti-clockwise direction.
    ShaftRateOfChange HLAinteger16BERPM_slsh_sperfectalways1 The rate of change of shaft speed. The shaft will change its rotational speed at this rate if the current shaft speed differs from the ordered shaft rate.
    Used by
